## Instructions

You need to build a silent chrome extension that will work in the background and will identify when these tabs are open but are no longer needed:

1. For zoom \- if it was open for over 10 minutes  
2. For teams \- if it was open for over 10 minutes  
3. For meet \- if the tab was already in a meeting (history would contain a meeting URL \- https://meet.google.com/sfg-bcmp-ugm?authuser=0 ) and is now in the Google Meet home page

Also I want to have a counter for the chrome extension so if I click on the chrome extension icon from the extensions dropdown it shows me how many tabs it closed for me
